1
00:01:13,740 --> 00:01:18,400
<i>[Meet Yourself]</i>

2
00:01:19,300 --> 00:01:23,840
<i>[Episode 35]</i>

3
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:47,880
He always coddles me with these weird things.

4
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:50,340
Does he think I'm a child?

5
00:02:24,100 --> 00:02:27,620
♫ <i>I've been alone</i> ♫

6
00:02:27,620 --> 00:02:30,899
<i>[Chairman Xie, a 15% discount is pushing it.]</i>
♫ <i>Into the unknown</i> ♫

7
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:37,940
<i>[Where can you find such a big buyer like me now?]</i>
♫ <i>Can navigate through the dark</i> ♫

8
00:02:38,660 --> 00:02:45,499
♫ <i>I'm searching for a meadow of mine</i> ♫

9
00:02:45,499 --> 00:02:52,099
♫ <i>Till you came in with the breeze</i> ♫

10
00:02:52,099 --> 00:02:55,239
♫ <i>A feeling rushes over me</i> ♫

11
00:02:55,239 --> 00:02:59,840
♫ <i>Spills my heart into the field</i> ♫

12
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:06,860
<i>[Receiving a ring for the second time in my life]</i>
♫ <i>I know it, I will be yours</i> ♫

13
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:11,800
The second time?

14
00:03:18,380 --> 00:03:21,340
<i>[Who was the first person who gave it to you?]</i>

15
00:03:42,020 --> 00:03:46,839
I'm serious. I really can't stand my dad. You know

16
00:03:46,839 --> 00:03:52,639
if I posted his deeds on the internet, he'd receive over 3,000 bad comments.

17
00:03:52,639 --> 00:03:54,680
Take Cuo Bazi as an example.

18
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:56,319
I told him from the very start that I wouldn't walk him.

19
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:58,400
The owner is supposed to walk the dog. Right?

20
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:01,560
My dad really threw him out.

21
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:03,879
When he brought the dog downstairs, he even said,

22
00:04:03,879 --> 00:04:06,340
"Your sister doesn't want you."

23
00:04:06,340 --> 00:04:08,540
I felt myself suffocating.

24
00:04:08,540 --> 00:04:09,599
Your life is great.

25
00:04:09,599 --> 00:04:12,819
Other kids want to raise a dog, but their parents won't let them.

26
00:04:12,819 --> 00:04:14,500
You know what?

27
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:17,620
When I was little, I raised two rabbits.

28
00:04:17,620 --> 00:04:20,660
My sister hated them.

29
00:04:20,660 --> 00:04:22,760
Have you seen rabbit poop?

30
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:24,840
Those round pellets.

31
00:04:25,380 --> 00:04:26,999
Aren't they dollops?

32
00:04:26,999 --> 00:04:28,359
Nope.

33
00:04:28,359 --> 00:04:30,119
A little smaller than sheep droppings.

34
00:04:30,119 --> 00:04:31,640
Small, round beads.

35
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:37,059
If you're near-sighted, you'd mistake them for chocolate beans.

36
00:04:37,059 --> 00:04:39,499
I'm a big fan of chocolate.

37
00:04:39,499 --> 00:04:41,940
Your metaphor is traumatizing me.

38
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:44,740
By the way, Hongdou,

39
00:04:44,740 --> 00:04:46,719
we saw the your post on WeChat Moments.

40
00:04:46,719 --> 00:04:49,439
You said this is the second ring you've received.

41
00:04:49,439 --> 00:04:53,740
In that case, when was the first time?

42
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:59,340
Is there a story?

43
00:04:59,340 --> 00:05:01,380
There is.

44
00:05:05,540 --> 00:05:08,580
But it's not what you guys are thinking.

45
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:13,400
The first person who gave me a ring

46
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:17,540
was my best friend.

47
00:05:17,540 --> 00:05:19,880
Her name is Chen Nanxing.

48
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:25,460
We went to college together.

49
00:05:25,460 --> 00:05:29,360
We even shared a room with each other for four years.

50
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:32,520
Both of us remained in Beijing...

51
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:35,800
and supported each other.

52
00:05:37,180 --> 00:05:39,660
It's a friendship that lasted over a decade.

53
00:05:42,520 --> 00:05:44,579
You have a homestay here now.

54
00:05:44,580 --> 00:05:46,640
Invite her over someday.

55
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:48,220
She can't come.

56
00:05:48,220 --> 00:05:49,339
Is she too busy with work to take a holiday?

57
00:05:49,340 --> 00:05:50,620
No, that's not it.

58
00:05:50,620 --> 00:05:53,000
She passed away last year.

59
00:06:02,620 --> 00:06:04,200
I'm sorry.

60
00:06:04,780 --> 00:06:06,460
It's fine.

61
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:11,580
Actually, I really wanted to share this with you.

62
00:06:11,580 --> 00:06:15,140
That's because you're my dear friends.

63
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:20,540
I hope she can live on in another way.

64
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:26,040
Every time her name is mentioned...

65
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:28,580
or her stories...

66
00:06:29,660 --> 00:06:33,760
are circulating among us,

67
00:06:34,440 --> 00:06:37,440
she will always exist.

68
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:39,480
Why am I crying again?

69
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:42,779
I'm sorry. Xie Zhiyao told me this.

70
00:06:42,779 --> 00:06:44,199
I'm not sure if I'm quoting him accurately.

71
00:06:44,199 --> 00:06:46,000
It's more or less this.

72
00:06:49,160 --> 00:06:51,600
I get it.

73
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:56,520
Right now, she exists in here.

74
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:58,580
Chen...

75
00:06:58,580 --> 00:06:59,879
Chen Nanxing.

76
00:06:59,879 --> 00:07:01,560
Nanxing.

77
00:07:06,140 --> 00:07:08,420
Nanxing for the southern star.

78
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:10,500
No, that's not right.

79
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:13,100
It stands for arum lilies.

80
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:18,140
♫ <i>Listen to the rain falling into the silent forest</i> ♫

81
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:25,420
♫ <i>Enjoy the mountainous landscape at sunset</i> ♫

82
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:34,180
♫ <i>The raindrops from the roof drip into my eyes quietly</i> ♫

83
00:07:34,180 --> 00:07:39,440
♫ <i>The world is like a quiet island</i> ♫

84
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:56,240
Na Na, are you still asleep?

85
00:08:02,380 --> 00:08:04,500
What's wrong, Mr. Ma?

86
00:08:04,500 --> 00:08:06,520
I'm going to leave.

87
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:08,580
Keep this.

88
00:08:11,900 --> 00:08:14,960
A master gave it to me.

89
00:08:14,960 --> 00:08:17,519
It turns ill luck into good fortune and calamities into blessings.

90
00:08:17,519 --> 00:08:19,520
Make sure you don't lose it.

91
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:25,560
Na Na, keep an open mind.

92
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:28,080
Walk when you can't run.

93
00:08:28,080 --> 00:08:30,920
When you can't run, meditate.

94
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:33,120
All mountains can be conquered somehow.

95
00:08:35,980 --> 00:08:37,460
You're clearly still in dreamland.

96
00:08:37,460 --> 00:08:38,739
Go back to sleep.

97
00:08:38,740 --> 00:08:40,480
I'm leaving.

98
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:59,440
Thank you, Mr. Ma.

99
00:09:08,420 --> 00:09:10,659
<i>He was still drowsy when we came out of there.</i>

100
00:09:10,660 --> 00:09:11,680
<i>Who's that?</i>

101
00:09:11,680 --> 00:09:12,979
<i>Where is this place?</i>

102
00:09:12,980 --> 00:09:14,359
<i>Impossible.</i>

103
00:09:14,359 --> 00:09:16,719
<i>Well, that person isn't important. Did you stay up all night?</i>

104
00:09:16,719 --> 00:09:17,820
<i>- That was you.
- Really?</i>

105
00:09:17,820 --> 00:09:19,460
<i>- Yeah.
- All right, enough about me.</i>

106
00:09:19,460 --> 00:09:23,779
<i>Your ex-boyfriend from college screamed your name outside your dormitory</i>

107
00:09:23,779 --> 00:09:24,999
<i>in the middle of the night.</i>

108
00:09:24,999 --> 00:09:26,679
<i>The one who lit candles downstairs, right?</i>

109
00:09:26,679 --> 00:09:28,260
<i>Yes! He also lit candles.</i>

110
00:09:28,260 --> 00:09:29,580
<i>Enough about that. Don't mention that again.</i>

111
00:09:29,580 --> 00:09:30,639
Don't talk badly about my girlfriend.

112
00:09:30,639 --> 00:09:34,200
In the middle of the night, your ex-boyfriend also...

113
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:36,240
Which one are you talking about?

114
00:09:41,060 --> 00:09:42,800
Mr. Hu!

115
00:09:43,880 --> 00:09:45,580
You're back!

116
00:09:45,580 --> 00:09:47,500
Heading to the kindergarten?

117
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:50,680
Are these two your friends?

118
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:52,860
My college classmates.

119
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:54,980
Let me introduce him.

120
00:09:54,980 --> 00:09:58,000
This is Mr. Hu, my neighbor.

121
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:01,199
He sings at the bar every night, and he's a great singer.

122
00:10:01,199 --> 00:10:02,299
Hello, Mr. Hu.

123
00:10:02,300 --> 00:10:03,600
- Hi, Mr. Hu.
- Hello.

124
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:04,440
How about this?

125
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:06,460
Let's go sing together tonight. My treat.

126
00:10:06,460 --> 00:10:07,839
Well, maybe next time.

127
00:10:07,839 --> 00:10:10,579
We're taking a road trip to Meili to see the sunset in the snow mountains.

128
00:10:10,579 --> 00:10:11,620
That's right.

129
00:10:11,620 --> 00:10:14,300
Do you think Li Jianfeng will join us if I invite him?

130
00:10:14,300 --> 00:10:17,280
Tell him Bai Manjun is with us, and he'll definitely come.

131
00:10:17,280 --> 00:10:19,059
You're right. Nonsense.

132
00:10:19,059 --> 00:10:20,299
I'll text him.

133
00:10:20,300 --> 00:10:22,100
- Come on.
- Yes, do that. Let me take a look.

134
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:23,940
Don't send weird messages. Don't text him.

135
00:10:23,940 --> 00:10:25,179
You're not stopping me.

136
00:10:25,180 --> 00:10:28,519
The other day, he told me he remembered everything between you two.

137
00:10:28,519 --> 00:10:29,899
He's still single.

138
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:31,279
Don't you think it's because of you?

139
00:10:31,279 --> 00:10:32,219
Yeah.

140
00:10:32,220 --> 00:10:33,579
<i>What does that have to do with me?</i>

141
00:10:33,580 --> 00:10:34,760
<i>Do you remember? When we were in college—</i>

142
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:36,640
<i>- Don't talk nonsense.
- He gave you a love letter!</i>

143
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:37,900
<i>Yeah!</i>

144
00:10:37,900 --> 00:10:38,959
<i>I wrote the letter for him.</i>

145
00:10:38,959 --> 00:10:40,139
<i>What did you write in the letter?</i>

146
00:10:40,140 --> 00:10:41,959
<i>That's enough, you two.</i>

147
00:10:41,959 --> 00:10:45,540
<i>A strand of your hair brushed against my cheek.</i>

148
00:10:45,540 --> 00:10:48,320
I don't want to use non-slip mats in the shower room.

149
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:49,660
I want this.

150
00:10:49,660 --> 00:10:52,240
Wooden mats made of antiseptic wood.

151
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:56,799
These will do as well, but they aren't easy to clean.

152
00:10:56,799 --> 00:10:58,439
Yes, we have to dismantle them each time,

153
00:10:58,439 --> 00:11:00,960
but these are far more comfortable to step on.

154
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:02,399
Okay, let's go with this.

155
00:11:02,399 --> 00:11:03,999
I'll take the measurements and let you know.

156
00:11:03,999 --> 00:11:05,440
Okay.

157
00:11:09,860 --> 00:11:12,280
Why didn't you reply to my message?

158
00:11:12,820 --> 00:11:15,759
Where are you going? Aren't you supposed to be shopping?

159
00:11:15,759 --> 00:11:17,039
I just got back from the horse ranch.

160
00:11:17,039 --> 00:11:19,180
I'll go after I send Cutie Pie back.

161
00:11:19,180 --> 00:11:20,940
Well, get going.

162
00:11:20,940 --> 00:11:23,139
Xiaochun is unloading at the warehouse today.

163
00:11:23,140 --> 00:11:26,079
Xiao Xin is alone in the cafe. She's all alone, so I'm going to help her.

164
00:11:26,079 --> 00:11:28,800
Why didn't you reply to my message?

165
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:32,719
I was drinking with Na Na in her room last night and my phone was charging.

166
00:11:33,540 --> 00:11:36,000
But you didn't reply to me this morning.

167
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:38,799
I did that on purpose. Stop asking.

168
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:40,900
Why didn't you reply?

169
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:43,260
Who was the first ring from?

170
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:45,040
I'm not going to tell you.

171
00:11:45,040 --> 00:11:48,999
I'll make you feel anxious, worried, agonized, and jittery.

172
00:11:48,999 --> 00:11:52,439
That was how I felt yesterday

173
00:11:52,439 --> 00:11:54,359
when you suggested that Na Na help you sell goods through live streaming.

174
00:11:54,359 --> 00:11:56,420
You can have a taste of it.

175
00:11:56,940 --> 00:11:59,520
Hold on. Why are you still holding a grudge?

176
00:11:59,520 --> 00:12:00,679
Just tell me.

177
00:12:00,679 --> 00:12:02,480
I won't. I'm busy. Take care.

178
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:04,999
- Goodbye.
- I'm childish?

179
00:12:04,999 --> 00:12:06,340
Aren't you more childish than me?

180
00:12:06,340 --> 00:12:09,079
You're wandering around on a horse during the day.

181
00:12:09,079 --> 00:12:10,999
I didn't even say you're a braggart.

182
00:12:10,999 --> 00:12:13,920
There are modern means of transport around, okay?

183
00:12:14,820 --> 00:12:16,200
You're the biggest baby around.

184
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:20,019
A grass ring? Do you think you can fool me with that?

185
00:12:20,019 --> 00:12:22,180
How about money?

186
00:12:22,180 --> 00:12:23,519
Make some money first.

187
00:12:23,519 --> 00:12:25,179
You sure are smug.

188
00:12:25,180 --> 00:12:27,360
Riding a white horse in the streets during the day.

189
00:12:27,360 --> 00:12:29,360
I'm doing this so I can meet you.

190
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:31,239
I'm going to Baoshan on business today, and I'll stay there for a night.

191
00:12:31,239 --> 00:12:32,880
I'm not coming back tonight.

192
00:12:32,880 --> 00:12:36,000
I hope you and Daxia have a safe trip.

193
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:39,680
How clingy.

194
00:12:43,260 --> 00:12:44,559
Chen Nanxing gave me the ring.

195
00:12:44,559 --> 00:12:46,440
Chen Nanxing!

196
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:09,800
Be careful, it's hot.

197
00:13:13,140 --> 00:13:14,840
No way. Are these people crazy?

198
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:16,419
Shall we unplug the phone?

199
00:13:16,420 --> 00:13:18,260
We did that yesterday, didn't we?

200
00:13:18,260 --> 00:13:22,040
I saw that it was unplugged in the morning, so I plugged it back.

201
00:13:25,660 --> 00:13:27,600
Hello, how can I help you?

202
00:13:28,820 --> 00:13:31,759
Sorry. We don't know this person.

203
00:13:44,340 --> 00:13:45,640
Your refreshments.

204
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:48,180
When you finish the tea, you can ask us to refill the water.

205
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:51,980
Is Nana-chan doing well?

206
00:13:51,980 --> 00:13:53,880
She's doing fine.

207
00:13:53,880 --> 00:13:56,880
Has she been a waitress here for the past year?

208
00:13:57,740 --> 00:14:01,540
- Do you want some honey in the tea?
- No, thanks.

209
00:14:01,540 --> 00:14:03,980
All right. Please enjoy.

210
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:09,479
"The hero is too weak."

211
00:14:09,479 --> 00:14:11,779
"He's waiting for the heroine to rescue him?"

212
00:14:11,780 --> 00:14:13,999
"I don't want to read it anymore."

213
00:14:13,999 --> 00:14:17,440
"Was the author's brain eaten by zombies?"

214
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:18,999
How is he weak?

215
00:14:18,999 --> 00:14:22,840
A team should work together to battle the enemy.

216
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:25,599
"The heroine was utterly trashed."

217
00:14:25,599 --> 00:14:28,379
"Is Damai Cha very ugly, too?"

218
00:14:28,380 --> 00:14:30,379
"She's just venting on society. It's hard to imagine this scene."

219
00:14:30,379 --> 00:14:31,999
"Horrible work. Stop writing."

220
00:14:31,999 --> 00:14:34,160
What's the matter with him?

221
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:35,280
There's this one as well.

222
00:14:35,280 --> 00:14:37,299
"Too much foreshadowing."

223
00:14:37,299 --> 00:14:38,839
"It's neither exciting nor sweet."

224
00:14:38,839 --> 00:14:40,439
"Both the hero and heroine have exes."

225
00:14:40,439 --> 00:14:42,020
"Is such characterization even necessary?

226
00:14:42,020 --> 00:14:43,650
So gross."

227
00:14:44,700 --> 00:14:46,020
This is funny.

228
00:14:46,020 --> 00:14:49,999
"Is the heroine also a musclebrain? All she does is fight."

229
00:14:49,999 --> 00:14:53,519
"Damai Cha has a record of celebrating violence."

230
00:14:53,519 --> 00:14:56,360
You like to celebrate violence?

231
00:14:57,140 --> 00:15:00,280
Stop reading these awful comments to me.

232
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:03,999
These are mild comments.

233
00:15:03,999 --> 00:15:05,479
They aren't awful.

234
00:15:05,479 --> 00:15:08,900
Besides, they paid money to read the chapters.

235
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:12,799
I didn't even recite a single one

236
00:15:12,799 --> 00:15:16,599
of those awful reviews, complaints, and comments saying they want me dead.

237
00:15:18,040 --> 00:15:19,380
I know.

238
00:15:19,380 --> 00:15:24,640
But I just have a feeling that's hard to describe.

239
00:15:30,120 --> 00:15:34,240
Na Na, I'm going to tell you something, but you can't get mad at me.

240
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:36,080
What is it?

241
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:42,199
After I found out what happened to you,

242
00:15:42,199 --> 00:15:45,780
I felt the distance between us shrink immensely.

243
00:15:45,780 --> 00:15:50,279
We've witnessed the same world

244
00:15:50,279 --> 00:15:52,439
and suffered the crushing weight of verbal abuse and harassment.

245
00:15:52,439 --> 00:15:53,960
Don't you agree?

246
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:58,080
You can empathize with me, can't you?

247
00:15:58,080 --> 00:15:59,279
So can you.

248
00:15:59,279 --> 00:16:03,019
You helped me so much. Wasn't that because you could empathize?

249
00:16:04,280 --> 00:16:08,080
I just... wanted you to pull yourself up.

250
00:16:10,420 --> 00:16:12,480
I want to do the same.

251
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:16,319
So, you should believe that once you survive this battle,

252
00:16:16,319 --> 00:16:20,340
you'll be able to get yourself together and move on.

253
00:16:26,460 --> 00:16:28,160
Don't come over! Don't come over!

254
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:29,900
It's Cuo Bazi.

255
00:16:35,260 --> 00:16:36,119
Hold it down.

256
00:16:36,119 --> 00:16:37,880
Make sure it doesn't move.

257
