527
00:30:20,100 --> 00:30:22,600
Mom! Why did you bring this up?

528
00:30:22,600 --> 00:30:25,800
She's not talking bad about you.

529
00:30:25,800 --> 00:30:28,000
Granny always tells me on the phone

530
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:30,300
about Hongdou accompanying her at her stall

531
00:30:30,300 --> 00:30:32,800
or Hongdou chatting with her.

532
00:30:32,800 --> 00:30:35,600
Hongdou even bought her toys.

533
00:30:35,600 --> 00:30:39,200
She loves you to bits. Right, Mom?

534
00:30:39,200 --> 00:30:40,000
Yeah.

535
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:42,200
She phoned us the other day to say

536
00:30:42,200 --> 00:30:44,800
you two started dating.

537
00:30:44,800 --> 00:30:48,000
All of us were thrilled!

538
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:50,300
- Hongdou, here's a toast to you.
- Thank you, Aunty.

539
00:30:50,300 --> 00:30:53,300
I wish you and A'Yao all the best for your careers and relationship.

540
00:30:53,300 --> 00:30:55,200
Good luck!

541
00:30:55,200 --> 00:30:56,900
Aunty and Uncle, thank you.

542
00:30:56,900 --> 00:30:58,400
Don't worry.

543
00:30:58,400 --> 00:31:00,600
I'll treat him well.

544
00:31:00,600 --> 00:31:01,800
You said this yourself.

545
00:31:01,800 --> 00:31:05,200
If you treat me poorly, I'll call my aunty.

546
00:31:05,200 --> 00:31:07,800
If Hongdou treats you poorly, reflect on yourself.

547
00:31:07,800 --> 00:31:09,000
How can you tell on her?

548
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:10,400
Exactly.

549
00:31:10,400 --> 00:31:11,400
That's right.

550
00:31:11,400 --> 00:31:13,500
She won't treat you poorly for no reason.

551
00:31:13,500 --> 00:31:14,700
Yeah.

552
00:31:14,700 --> 00:31:19,400
I'm just like spilled water you guys don't care about, right?

553
00:31:19,400 --> 00:31:20,600
Watch it.

554
00:31:20,600 --> 00:31:21,400
Isn't that right?

555
00:31:21,400 --> 00:31:23,700
This water has drenched me.

556
00:31:24,500 --> 00:31:25,600
Let's eat.

557
00:31:25,600 --> 00:31:26,700
Have some vegetables.

558
00:31:26,700 --> 00:31:28,200
Thank you.

559
00:31:28,200 --> 00:31:29,200
Eat whatever you like.

560
00:31:29,200 --> 00:31:30,300
If you don't like it, leave it.

561
00:31:30,300 --> 00:31:31,700
Okay.

562
00:31:33,800 --> 00:31:35,400
- Granny, have some too.
- Do you want fish balls?

563
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:37,200
Let me get you a fish ball.

564
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:38,200
Let's all get it for her.

565
00:31:38,200 --> 00:31:39,500
Eat mine, Granny!

566
00:31:39,500 --> 00:31:40,400
Okay.

567
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:43,000
♫ <i>Slim and elegant</i> ♫

568
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:47,000
♫ <i>My baby, time to sleep</i> ♫

569
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:54,500
I should help them.

570
00:31:54,500 --> 00:31:55,800
Sit down.

571
00:31:55,800 --> 00:31:57,200
Drink your tea.

572
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:01,500
Hongdou, the fruits are ready.

573
00:32:02,400 --> 00:32:04,400
Have some.

574
00:32:04,400 --> 00:32:05,800
Lanzhi,

575
00:32:05,800 --> 00:32:07,400
I'm going to visit Grandpa Yang.

576
00:32:07,400 --> 00:32:08,400
Going to drink?

577
00:32:08,400 --> 00:32:10,000
Nope.

578
00:32:14,200 --> 00:32:15,800
Only a little.

579
00:32:15,800 --> 00:32:16,800
Get going.

580
00:32:16,800 --> 00:32:18,200
Hongdou, enjoy yourself here.

581
00:32:18,200 --> 00:32:20,500
- Okay, Uncle.
- I'm heading out.

582
00:32:21,260 --> 00:32:23,499
He doesn't know any of our neighbors in Kunming.

583
00:32:23,500 --> 00:32:25,000
He must've been yearning for friends.

584
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:28,500
Every time we come back here, he goes missing at night.

585
00:32:28,500 --> 00:32:30,600
He's always visiting people.

586
00:32:30,600 --> 00:32:32,200
Uncle!

587
00:32:32,200 --> 00:32:33,300
Look at this house.

588
00:32:33,300 --> 00:32:34,600
How wonderful.

589
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:36,900
All your furniture is new.

590
00:32:37,800 --> 00:32:39,800
Deqing and his wife are filial as well.

591
00:32:39,800 --> 00:32:41,800
Why are you still clamoring to move out?

592
00:32:41,800 --> 00:32:43,800
Why are you making a fuss?

593
00:32:45,600 --> 00:32:47,200
- A'Qing.
- Uncle.

594
00:32:47,200 --> 00:32:48,800
How are you doing in school?

595
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:50,200
Not bad.

596
00:32:50,200 --> 00:32:52,800
Have you decided on which university you want to attend?

597
00:32:52,800 --> 00:32:54,600
Not yet, Uncle.

598
00:32:55,300 --> 00:32:58,800
Ask A'Yao to gather a list of good schools.

599
00:32:58,800 --> 00:33:00,000
- Okay.
- Off you go.

600
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:01,200
Tell your mom to stop cooking.

601
00:33:01,200 --> 00:33:02,700
It's enough.

602
00:33:03,900 --> 00:33:06,000
Call your dad over for drinks.

603
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:08,000
- Okay.
- Don't go.

604
00:33:08,600 --> 00:33:10,600
He better not show his face here.

605
00:33:10,600 --> 00:33:12,400
This scoundrel.

606
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:13,200
All right.

607
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:15,400
We won't let him join us.

608
00:33:15,400 --> 00:33:17,600
Uncle, come on.

609
00:33:17,600 --> 00:33:19,500
Let's drink.

610
00:33:19,500 --> 00:33:22,200
I haven't had a drink with you in a while.

611
00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:31,300
Why did Deqing ask you to come over?

612
00:33:32,600 --> 00:33:34,400
He didn't say a word.

613
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:38,900
A'Yao got himself a girlfriend.

614
00:33:38,900 --> 00:33:39,900
Lanzhi hasn't met her yet.

615
00:33:39,900 --> 00:33:41,600
We came to see her.

616
00:33:41,600 --> 00:33:42,800
A girlfriend?

617
00:33:42,800 --> 00:33:44,000
Where's she from?

618
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:45,500
From Beijing.

619
00:33:46,200 --> 00:33:48,400
His girlfriend bought

620
00:33:48,400 --> 00:33:51,000
the homestay under construction.

621
00:33:52,100 --> 00:33:53,600
In the past,

622
00:33:53,600 --> 00:33:55,800
he raised hell in the village with Xiao Huang.

623
00:33:55,800 --> 00:33:59,000
Now, there's one more person with him.

624
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:00,800
They only come together

625
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:04,600
to create a mess of the village.

626
00:34:04,600 --> 00:34:06,100
This place has lost all peace and quiet!

627
00:34:06,100 --> 00:34:08,300
You're just unaware.

628
00:34:08,300 --> 00:34:10,000
It's like they poked a hornets' nest.

629
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:13,200
Tourists are flooding this place.

630
00:34:13,200 --> 00:34:15,500
Isn't it nice to have more tourists?

631
00:34:15,500 --> 00:34:16,700
On my way here,

632
00:34:16,700 --> 00:34:20,000
I saw many stalls set up in front of the houses.

633
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:23,200
They were selling tie-dyed products and scarves.

634
00:34:23,200 --> 00:34:24,400
Yeah.

635
00:34:24,400 --> 00:34:26,000
They're all retailing products.

636
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:27,000
Well, who'll farm the lands?

637
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:29,000
What will we eat?

638
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:31,000
We'll still need to farm the lands.

639
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:32,800
They just have another source of income.

640
00:34:35,200 --> 00:34:36,500
Income?

641
00:34:36,500 --> 00:34:38,000
What income?

642
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:40,200
Money has filled their heads.

643
00:34:40,200 --> 00:34:41,800
Absurd.

644
00:34:46,400 --> 00:34:47,800
Uncle.

645
00:34:49,500 --> 00:34:53,400
When I was little, my brother fell sick.

646
00:34:53,400 --> 00:34:55,800
We had no money and had to borrow from you.

647
00:34:55,800 --> 00:34:57,200
You didn't have enough savings, so you helped us borrow money from others.

648
00:34:57,200 --> 00:35:00,000
It took us a lot of effort to scrape together the money.

649
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:03,000
However, medicine wasn't developed back then.

650
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:04,800
We spent loads of money on my brother,

651
00:35:06,800 --> 00:35:09,800
but he still didn't get cured.

652
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:13,700
When I grew up, I only remembered my family's poverty.

653
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:17,500
Life back then was so much worse.

654
00:35:19,200 --> 00:35:20,300
Education wasn't compulsory.

655
00:35:20,300 --> 00:35:23,100
We even had to scrimp and save to pay for school.

656
00:35:23,100 --> 00:35:25,600
You made Deqing take your money

657
00:35:25,600 --> 00:35:26,900
and drag me to school.

658
00:35:26,900 --> 00:35:28,300
I had disappointing grades,

659
00:35:28,300 --> 00:35:31,600
but at least I finished junior high.

660
00:35:32,800 --> 00:35:34,400
I'm not well-educated.

661
00:35:34,400 --> 00:35:36,600
My first wife and I...

662
00:35:37,900 --> 00:35:40,900
wanted A'Yao to study hard

663
00:35:40,900 --> 00:35:42,700
and leave this village.

664
00:35:43,400 --> 00:35:45,900
He's just like his mom.

665
00:35:45,900 --> 00:35:49,100
He's smart and went to university.

666
00:35:49,100 --> 00:35:52,200
He even clinched a well-paid job.

667
00:35:52,200 --> 00:35:57,000
My children were so close to escaping a life of farming,

668
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:02,000
but he insisted on coming back.

669
00:36:03,600 --> 00:36:04,800
In the first two years after he returned,

670
00:36:04,800 --> 00:36:07,200
I made life hell for him.

671
00:36:07,200 --> 00:36:09,800
The Bai Family's tie-dye workshop

672
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:12,400
was going broke, but he insisted on taking it over.

673
00:36:12,400 --> 00:36:15,000
I stopped him at the gates and yelled at him.

674
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:18,900
The police officers even came over!

675
00:36:20,800 --> 00:36:22,800
So embarrassing!

676
00:36:25,400 --> 00:36:29,200
But at that time,

677
00:36:29,200 --> 00:36:31,900
I'd willingly embarrass myself for his future.

678
00:36:35,500 --> 00:36:36,800
After that,

679
00:36:36,800 --> 00:36:39,200
Lanzhi told me this.

680
00:36:39,200 --> 00:36:42,000
Every generation does better than the one before.

681
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:43,900
We aren't well-educated,

682
00:36:43,900 --> 00:36:46,900
but A'Yao is a university graduate with broader visions.

683
00:36:46,900 --> 00:36:49,200
He doesn't see things the way we do.

684
00:36:49,200 --> 00:36:50,800
We have to trust him

685
00:36:50,800 --> 00:36:54,200
and seek his advice in troubling times.

686
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:58,000
Uncle, a majority of your peers were farmers

687
00:36:58,000 --> 00:36:59,600
and had little money.

688
00:36:59,600 --> 00:37:02,200
My peers can work in the cities.

689
00:37:02,200 --> 00:37:03,500
Life has become much better.

690
00:37:03,500 --> 00:37:06,000
However, the children and the elderly

691
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:08,600
are left behind at home.

692
00:37:08,600 --> 00:37:09,900
Look at the present situation.

693
00:37:09,900 --> 00:37:11,500
If we have more tourists,

694
00:37:11,500 --> 00:37:14,200
families can stay together at home

695
00:37:14,200 --> 00:37:16,800
and earn more money for a better life.

696
00:37:16,800 --> 00:37:18,600
Isn't that wonderful?

697
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:25,600
Siping, what do you think will happen

698
00:37:25,600 --> 00:37:27,600
to our village in the future?

699
00:37:30,300 --> 00:37:32,500
I don't know.

700
00:37:32,500 --> 00:37:35,100
I dare not imagine the future.

701
00:37:35,100 --> 00:37:37,000
A few years ago, no one would've thought about

702
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:39,200
selling flowers on a livestream.

703
00:37:39,200 --> 00:37:41,300
Delivery services are so fast.

704
00:37:41,300 --> 00:37:43,600
We don't even need to carry cash now.

705
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:50,600
Uncle, a person can't manage the lives of another generation.

706
00:37:50,600 --> 00:37:53,200
The world out there is changing rapidly.

707
00:37:53,200 --> 00:37:56,600
We should alter our thinking for the next generation

708
00:37:56,600 --> 00:37:58,800
and the generation after that.

709
00:37:58,800 --> 00:38:00,200
Don't you agree?

710
00:38:10,100 --> 00:38:11,900
Impressive, Uncle.

711
00:38:13,400 --> 00:38:15,400
Granny, I'm leaving.

712
00:38:21,400 --> 00:38:23,200
I want to take a flower with me.

713
00:38:23,200 --> 00:38:25,100
I'll remove the thorns for you.

714
00:38:36,800 --> 00:38:40,000
Here you go. I'll send them over to you tomorrow when they're ready.

715
00:38:41,200 --> 00:38:43,300
<i>Hongdou, wait!</i>

716
00:38:47,200 --> 00:38:49,800
This is a gift from me and A'Yaos dad.

717
00:38:49,800 --> 00:38:51,200
- Here, take it.
- No, I can't.

718
00:38:51,200 --> 00:38:53,200
I can't take this. Aunty, I really can't accept this.

719
00:38:53,200 --> 00:38:54,400
This is our first meeting.

720
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:56,800
You can't reject our red packet.

721
00:38:56,800 --> 00:38:58,700
There's no need, Aunty. This is too much.

722
00:38:58,700 --> 00:39:00,400
It isn't much. Take it.

723
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:02,500
Just take it.

724
00:39:02,500 --> 00:39:03,400
- A'Yao.
- Yeah?

725
00:39:03,400 --> 00:39:06,400
Once you walk Hongdou home, pick up your dad.

726
00:39:06,400 --> 00:39:07,600
He must've drunk a lot.

727
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:08,600
Okay.

728
00:39:08,600 --> 00:39:10,100
Aunty, thank you for today.

729
00:39:10,100 --> 00:39:11,400
The food was delicious.

730
00:39:11,400 --> 00:39:13,500
I'll teach A'Yao the dishes you enjoyed.

731
00:39:13,500 --> 00:39:15,600
Get him to cook for you.

732
00:39:15,600 --> 00:39:17,200
Let's go.

733
00:39:17,200 --> 00:39:18,200
Good night.

734
